{
  "texts": [
    "Nowotsch et al. [72] employ a measurement-based timing analysis approach to evaluate the impact of multi-core architectures on avionics systems.",
    "The experiments were conducted using a custom OS layer running bare-metal on the platform, ensuring full control and avoiding external interferences.",
    "By stressing the interconnect, system-level caches, and main memory through software-induced interference, the authors measure execution times using the cores' timebase registers in a controlled environment.",
    "This methodology allows for precise timing analysis, critical for assessing the feasibility and reliability of multi-core systems in safety-critical avionics applications.HYDTA methods use static analysis to identify potential execution paths that may not have been exercised during measurement, increasing the confidence that the WCET estimate covers all possible scenarios.",
    "By collecting measurements at a finer granularity, such as function or basic block level, HYDTA can provide more detailed insight into the execution behavior, allowing for a more accurate combination of static and dynamic information."
  ]
}